Name: big-normandy-campaign
PreviousDaysEventsDescription:
The Axis destroyed Conde sur Noireau Tank Repair Station and La Ferte Mace Troop Encampment.

A contingent of Allied paratroopers have been deployed to capture and secure Falaise Encampment.

Allied logistics resupplied Villedieu Fuel Depot, La Vielle, Vire Command And Logistics, and Carpiquet.

German logistics resupplied Rouen Rail Yards, Gournay en Bray Armour Repair Depot, Bolbec Aviation Fuel Logistics, and Chartres Coal Gas Processing Operation.
CurrentDayStateDescription:
The current situation

The Allies control airfields at Cretteville, Maupertus, Pontorson, and La Vielle. Allied airfield Carpiquet is heavily damaged.The Axis control airfields at Beaumont Le Roger, Le Havre Octeville, and Triqueville. German airfield Lonrai is heavily damaged.

Allied forces are stationed at Arromanches Mulberry B, Coutances Road and Rail Junction, Villedieu Fuel Depot, Vire Command And Logistics, and Domfront HFDF Site. The Allies are in poor shape at Saint Hilaire River Crossing. German forces control Saint-Valery-en-Caux Flak School, Bolbec Aviation Fuel Logistics, Cabourg Coastal Defences, Lisieux Ball Bearing Factory, Vimoutiers Sawmill and Logging Station, and L Aigle Supply Dump. The Axis have only a tenuous grip on Perche HFDF Testing Facility.

Allied convoys are likely to attempt to resupply Carpiquet. German convoys are reported to be en-route to resupply Perche HFDF Testing Facility.

Objectives.Name: Conde sur Noireau Tank Repair Station
